data.description: Location is everything, and this Cape Vista gem in West Bradenton offers the perfect blend of proximity and serenity. Approximately a 5-mile drive transports you to the pristine Gulf Beaches, where you can relish some of the most breathtaking sunsets Florida offers. Beyond the sandy shores, an array of attractions awaits, from Baseball Spring Training Facilities and the renowned IMG Academy to museums, recreation parks, tempting restaurants, shopping havens, and some of the best universities. Embark on a quick journey, and you'll find yourself in the cultural hub of Sarasota within minutes or heading north to the vibrant St. Petersburg in just 30. minutes. Looking for big-city adventures? Tampa is within easy reach, providing endless entertainment options within about an hour's drive. Nestled on a generous corner lot, this home boasts new vinyl fencing, creating a private backyard retreat. Step inside, and a thoughtfully designed split floor plan will greet you. Two bedrooms and a bathroom on one side offer privacy, while the opposite side showcases a multi-use flex room with its own bathroom and private outside entry. The possibilities are endless – a home office, guest suite, or even a creative studio. The interior has been treated to a fresh coat of paint, and new windows illuminate every corner of this Florida haven. Newly installed ceiling fans and new carpeting in all bedrooms add to the charm. The kitchen features a newer large double basin sink, updated cabinetry, and a convenient closet pantry. The kitchen flows seamlessly into the dining room, overlooking the living room. Through sliding glass doors, you'll discover a closed-in Lanai bathed in Florida sunshine, offering a perfect spot to relax and enjoy the view of the backyard. Now is the time to make this house your home. Bring your offers and step into the Florida lifestyle you've been dreaming of. Coastal living, convenience, and endless possibilities – it's all here. Make it yours today!
